20Federal%20Student%20Aid%2C%20known%20as%20FAFSA%2C%20forms%20to%20schools%20until%20early%20March.%20That's%20two%20months%20after%20it%20previously%20said%20it%20would%20begin%20sending%20over%20that%20data.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20delay%20means%20that%20it%20could%20take%20until%20April%20for%20some%20families%20to%20learn%20how%20much%20financial%20aid%20they'll%20receive%20%E2%80%94%20just%20one%20month%20before%20students%20have%20to%20confirm%20which%20college%20they'll%20be%20attending%20in%20the%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20delay%20is%20a%20result%20of%20the%20Education%20Department's%20efforts%20to%20overhaul%20the%20FAFSA%20form%20to%20make%20it%20simplified%20for%20families%20and%20students.%20While%20the%20form%20was%20released%20on%20October%201%20in%20prior%20years%2C%20the%20new%20release%20was%20delayed%20nearly%20three%20months%20later%20as%20the%20department%20was%20implementing%20a%20%26quot%3Bsoft-launch%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20delay%20in%20receiving%20financial%20aid%20awards%20can%20be%20attributed%20to%20the%20department's%20efforts%20to%20update%20FAFSA%20qualifications%20to%20expand%20families'%20financial%20aid%20eligibility.%20Specifically%2C%20the%20department%20said%20it%20would%20update%20FAFSA's%20%26quot%3BStudent%20Aid%20Index%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20determines%20how%20much%20a%20family%20can%20afford%20to%20pay%20for%20college.%20When%20the%20new%20FAFSA%20form%20was%20soft-launched%2C%20the%20formula%20relied%20on%20inflation%20figures%20from%202020%2C%20and%20the%20update%20is%20expected%20to%20open%20up%20an%20additional%20%241.8%20billion%20in%20federal%20student%20aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20that'll%20take%20time%20%E2%80%94%20and%20could%20leave%20some%20families%20in%20a%20time%20crunch%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20evaluating%20their%20financial%20aid%20packages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Better%20FAFSA%20makes%20it%20as%20simple%20and%20easy%20as%20possible%20for%20families%20to%20get%20help%20paying%20for%20college%2C%20and%20updating%20our%20tables%20will%20help%20even%20more%20students%20get%20the%20help%20they%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20Under%20Secretary%20of%20Education%20James%20Kvaal%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BUpdating%20our%20calculations%20will%20help%20students%20qualify%20for%20as%20much%20financial%20aid%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20delay%20has%20sparked%20concern%20among%20higher%20education%20advocates%20who%20say%20it'll%20leave%20insufficient%20time%20for%20families%20to%20make%20major%20financial%20choices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20the%20very%20day%20that%20schools%20were%20expecting%20FAFSA%20applicant%20information%2C%20they%20were%20instead%20notified%20by%20the%20U.S.%20Department%20of%20Education%20that%20they%20shouldn't%20expect%20to%20receive%20that%20data%20until%20March%2C%20at%20the%20earliest%2C%26quot%3B%20Justin%20Draeger%2C%20president%20of%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Student%20Financial%20Aid%20Administrators%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20continued%20delays%2C%20communicated%20at%20the%20last%20minute%2C%20threaten%20to%20harm%20the%20very%20students%20and%20families%20that%20federal%20student%20aid%20is%20intended%20to%20help%2C%26quot%3B%20Draeger%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENine%20higher%20education%20groups%20also%20called%20for%20colleges%20to%20extend%20the%20financial%20aid%20deadline%20beyond%20May%201%20to%20accommodate%20for%20the%20delays%2C%20saying%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.acenet.edu%2FNews-Room%2FPages%2FJoint-Statement-Financial-Aid-Deadlines.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejoint%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20all%20want%20students%20and%20families%20to%20have%20the%20time%20they%20need%20to%20consider%20their%20financial%20options%20before%20making%20enrollment%20decisions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Education%20Department%20said%20it%20would%20continue%20to%20update%20schools%20and%20stakeholders%20on%20FAFSA%20progress%20as%20it%20prepares%20to%20send%20information%20to%20schools%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20March.%20So%20far%2C%203.1%20million%20applications%20have%20successfully%20been%20submitted%2C%20the%20department%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGOP%20lawmakers%20requesting%20FAFSA%20oversight%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20precarious%20FAFSA%20rollout%20has%20prompted%20a%20number%20of%20Republican%20lawmakers%20to%20request%20additional%20information%20on%20why%20these%20delays%20are%20happening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20top%20Republican%20on%20the%20House%20education%20committee%20Virginia%20Foxx%20and%20chair%20of%20an%20education%20subcommittee%20Burgess%20Owens%20sent%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedworkforce.house.gov%2Fuploadedfiles%2Ffoxx_owens_fafsa.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Education%20Secretary%20Miguel%20Cardona%20requesting%20additional%20information%20on%20how%20it's%20rolling%20out%20the%20new%20FAFSA%20forms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThough%20the%20FAFSA%20is%20available%20today%20for%20completion%2C%20the%20Department%20itself%20has%20admitted%20that%20students%20and%20families%20are%20still%20unable%20to%20complete%20the%20FAFSA%20because%20of%20an%20extensive%20list%20of%20technical%20issues%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BMany%20of%20the%20issues%20have%20no%20current%20workarounds.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESen.%20Bill%20Cassidy%2C%20the%20top%20Republican%20on%20the%20Senate%20education%20committee%2C%20also%20released%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.help.senate.gov%2Franking%2Fnewsroom%2Fpress%2Franking-member-cassidy-sounds-alarm-over-biden-admin-delaying-fafsa-information-harming-students-access-to-financial-aid%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Tuesday%20saying%20that%20%26quot%3Bthese%20unacceptable%20delays%20from%20the%20Biden%20administration%20creates%20the%20real%20likelihood%20that%20many%20students%20will%20forgo%20college%20because%20they%20cannot%20choose%20a%20school%20without%20knowing%20their%20eligibility%20for%20student%20aid.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECassidy%20and%20Foxx%20led%2026%20of%20their%20colleagues%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.help.senate.gov%2Franking%2Fnewsroom%2Fpress%2Franking-member-cassidy-chairwoman-foxx-colleagues-request-investigation-into-biden-admins-botched-fafsa-rollout-impact-on-students-and-schools%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erequesting%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%20that%20the%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%20investigate%20the%20Education%20Department's%20FAFSA%20rollout%2C%20saying%20the%20delays%20could%20particularly%20harm%20low-income%20students%20who%20depend%20most%20on%20financial%20aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20department%20has%20not%20yet%20commented%20on%20the%20investigation%20and%20said%20it%20will%20continue%20moving%20forward%20with%20simplifying%20FAFSA%20for%20families%20reliant%20on%20financial%20aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20remain%20committed%20to%20ensuring%20students%20and%20families%20have%20stable%20and%20secure%20access%20to%20more%20than%20%24114%20billion%20in%20federal%20financial%20aid%2C%26quot%3B%20Federal%20Student%20Aid%20Chief%20Richard%20Cordray%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20how%20crucial%20this%20support%20is%20to%20pursue%20higher%20education%2C%20particularly%20for%20the%20most%20underserved%20communities%2C%20and%20the%20positive%20ripple%20effects%20an%20education%20beyond%20high%20school%20makes%20in%20the%20lives%20of%20millions%2C%20their%20communities%2C%20and%20the%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffafsa-why-parents-students-have-to-wait-financial-aid-awards-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706784421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22h