%2F6550920%2Fworld-elections-2024%2F%5C%22%3Eat%20least%2064%20countries%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20ask%20their%20citizens%20to%20elect%20a%20government%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20keenly%20observed%20will%20be%20the%20United%20Kingdom%20general%20election%2C%20likely%20to%20be%20held%20in%20November.%20The%20British%20Labour%20party%20has%20not%20won%20an%20election%20since%202010%2C%20and%20has%20lost%20the%20last%20four%20elections.%20At%20the%20last%20election%20in%202019%2C%20it%20was%20beaten%20handsomely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202019%20result%20saw%20the%20Conservatives%20win%20365%20seats%20of%20the%20650%20seats%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%2C%20while%20Labour%20limped%20in%20with%20202%20seats.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20Boris%20Johnson%20was%20an%20immensely%20popular%20political%20leader%2C%20single-handedly%20delivering%20the%20Conservatives%20a%20historic%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFamously%2C%20Johnson%20broke%20down%20part%20of%20Labour%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fpolitics%2F2023%2Fdec%2F11%2Fkeir-starmer-promises-red-wall-voters-the-basics-of-government-done-better%5C%22%3Ered%20wall%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20seats%20%E2%80%93%20historically%20safe%20Labour%20seats%20in%20parts%20of%20Northern%20England.%20With%20Johnson%E2%80%99s%20emphatic%20win%2C%20and%20Brexit%20%E2%80%9Cdone%E2%80%9D%2C%20one%20writer%20predicted%20a%20further%20%E2%80%9Cdecade%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fbooks%2Friding-the-populist-wave%2F4D4C82C02F8A80A03FD2EC18B5D8CACD%5C%22%3Econservative%20dominance%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20the%20decade%20of%20conservative%20dominance%20did%20not%20arrive%2C%20and%20on%20current%20reading%2C%20the%20Conservatives%20look%20destined%20for%20opposition.%20The%20most%20recent%20poll%20confirms%20Labour%E2%80%99s%20long-standing%2020-point%20lead%20over%20the%20Conservatives%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Feurope-poll-of-polls%2Funited-kingdom%2F%5C%22%3E(45%25-25%25)%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Since%20the%20Brexit%20Referendum%2C%20there%20has%20been%20unprecedented%20volatility%20in%20British%20politics%20%E2%80%93%20not%20dissimilar%20to%20the%20leadership%20churn%20in%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%202016%20referendum%2C%20the%20Conservatives%20have%20chewed%20through%20five%20different%20leaders%20from%20David%20Cameron%20to%20Rishi%20Sunak.%20Each%20successive%20leader%20has%20been%20ensnared%20in%20a%20range%20of%20crises%2C%20from%20Theresa%20May%E2%80%99s%20record%20common%20defeats%20over%20Brexit%2C%20Johnson%E2%80%99s%20handling%20of%20COVID%2C%20Sunak%E2%80%99s%20problems%20with%20inflation%2C%20and%20of%20course%2C%20the%20blitzkrieg%20politics%20of%20shock%20and%20incompetence%20of%20Liz%20Truss.%20The%20Conservative%20party%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fbattles-on-the-backbenches-what-are-the-different-factions-in-the-conservative-party-12964275%5C%22%3Efragmented%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20factionalised%2C%20with%20the%20hardline%20right%20pushing%20to%20veto%20key%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22440%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FF81x3f7t07o%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22260%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20volatility%20has%20led%20to%20wider%20governing%20instability.%20Since%202019%2C%20there%20have%20been%20five%20home%20secretaries%2C%20and%20a%20remarkable%20six%20chancellors%20(the%20role%20of%20federal%20treasurer%20in%20Australia).%20This%20turmoil%20takes%20an%20incalculable%20toll%20on%20effective%20government%2C%20as%20policy%20settings%20continuously%20change%2C%20and%20the%20public%20service%20are%20left%20reeling%20in%20the%20aftermath.%20For%20the%20Johnson%20government%20in%20particular%2C%20personal%20loyalty%20and