ultant.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20explains%20that%20highly%20paid%20executives%20don't%20take%20pay%20cuts%20because%20it%20wouldn't%20make%20a%20significant%20difference.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECompanies%20load%20up%20execs%20with%20stock%20because%20they%20don't%20cost%20the%20business%20money%20out%20of%20pocket.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20all%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-sweeping-us-these-are-companies-making-cuts-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elayoffs%20in%20the%20news%3C%2Fa%3E%20we're%20seeing%2C%20there's%20always%20the%20question%3A%20Why%20don't%20the%20highly%20paid%20executives%20take%20a%20pay%20cut%3F%20Couldn't%20they%20trim%20their%20massive%20pay%20packages%20and%20save%20some%20jobs%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20over%2040%20years%20in%20business%2C%20including%20being%20the%20VP%20of%20HR%20for%20Microsoft%2C%20I've%20seen%20more%20than%20a%20few%20layoffs.%20This%20observation%20is%20a%20fair%20one.%20The%20executives%20in%20charge%20never%20seem%20to%20pay%20a%20price%20for%20the%20pain%20they%20cause%2C%20and%20here%20are%20several%20reasons%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20It's%20just%20math%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%2C%20the%20reason%20executives%20most%20commonly%20use%20to%20justify%20it%20to%20themselves%2C%20is%20simple%20math.%20Cutting%20their%20salary%20wouldn't%20make%20a%20significant%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20Google%20or%20Microsoft%20for%20example%2C%20two%20companies%20with%20very%20similar%20math.%20These%20companies%20both%20have%20around%20200%2C000%20employees.%20Both%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-employees-fight-back-layoffs-just-business-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elaid%20off%20somewhere%20around%2010%2C000%20employees%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20last%20year%20or%20so.%20And%20both%20CEOs%20are%20paid%20similar%20amounts%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2FArchives%2Fedgar%2Fdata%2F1652044%2F000130817922000262%2Flgoog2022_def14a.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esalaries%20of%20around%20%242%20million%20a%20year%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20these%20companies%2C%20cutting%2010%2C000%20employees%20saves%20them%20in%20the%20neighborhood%20of%20a%20billion%20dollars%20a%20year%20in%20costs.%20Cutting%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwage-gap-executive-compensation-ceo-pay-ratio-workers-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECEO's%20salary%3C%2Fa%3E%20entirely%20would%20save%20just%200.2%25%20of%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20math%20is%20so%20large%2C%20that%20executives%20like%20to%20point%20out%20that%20cutting%20their%20salary%20wouldn't%20even%20put%20a%20dent%20in%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20It's%20about%20stock%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20wait%2C%20you%20protest%2C%20Google's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falphabet-ceo-sundar-pichai-pay-soars-226-million-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESundar%20Pichai%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20over%20%24200%20million%20last%20year!%20And%20Microsoft's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsatya-nadella-life-career-microsoft-ceo-computer-science-2024-1%23a-decade-as-ceo-21%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESatya%20Nadella%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20almost%20%2450%20million%20in%202022!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20what%20makes%20the%20news%2C%20but%20it's%20really%20not%20what%20is%20happening.%20They%20were%20not%20paid%20these%20amounts%3B%20they%20were%20given%20stock%20grants.%20Grants%20that%20vest%20(become%20exercisable)%20over%20a%20period%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESundar's%20for%20example%2C%20vests%20over%20three%20years.%20If%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fgoogl-stock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20stock%20price%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20to%20plummet%2C%20so%20would%20his%20compensation.%20But%20it%20soared%2C%20up%20by%20about%2050%25%20in%20the%20last%20year.%20Sundar%20did%20exceptionally%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20kinds%20of%20grants%20are%20common%20in%20executive%20compensation%20because%20the%20companies%20like%20them.%20The%20stock%20doesn't%20cost%20the%20company%20this%20money%20out%20of%20pocket.%20Accounting%20magic%20makes%20these%20kinds%20of%20grants%20very%20cheap%20for%20the%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20importantly%2C%20boards%20see%20handcuffing%20the%20executive%20to%20the%20stock%20price%20roller%20coaster%20as%20a%20good%20thing.%20If%20the%20CEO%20doesn't%20fix%20the%20cost%20problem%2C%20their%20compensation%20takes%20a%20huge%20hit.%20If%20they%20take%20action%20that%20increases%20the%20company's%20value%20and%20its%20stock%20price%2C%20everyone%20wins.%20Or%20at%20least%20all%20the%20stockholders%20win%2C%20which%20includes%20the%20executive%2C%20the%20board%2C%20many%20employees%2C%20and%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20like%20the%20salary%2C%20because%20these%20grants%20don't%20affect%20the%20current%20bottom%20line%2C%20cutting%20them%20won't%20save%20the%20money%20they%20need%20to%20trim.%20The%20company%2C%20the%20board%2C%20and%20the%20CEO%20will%20say%20when%20asked%20that%20it%20wouldn't%20make%20a%20dent%20in%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20It's%20the%20competition%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20factor%20is%20the%20fierce%20competition%20for%20talent%20for%20these%20executive%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20like%20in%20the%20sports%20world%2C%20very%20few%20people%20can%20play%20at%20this%20level.%20Precious%20few%20executives%20have%20the%20experience%20to%20lead%20nearly%20trillion-dollar%20companies%2C%20with%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20employees%20and%20operations%20on%20a%20global%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20star%20athletes%2C%20those%20who%20can%20perform%20at%20this%20level%20look%20to%20their%20peers.%20They%20compare%20and%20contrast%2C%20often%20with%20envy.%20There's%20a%20reason%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffortune.com%2F2023%2F08%2F04%2Fceo-worker-pay-gap-ratio-afl-cio-report-highest-paid-ceo-america-tim-cook-sundar-pichai-apple-live-nation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebase%20compensation%20in%20the%20Fortune%20500%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20very%20similar.%20The%20talent%20competition%20is%20tight%2C%20and%20those%20who%20play%20at%20that%20level%20know%20their%20worth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20difference%20then%20is%20the%20stock%20package%20and%20the%20stock%20price%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0just%20what%20the%20boards%20of%20these%20companies%20want.%20They%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20hire%20a%20star%2C%20load%20them%20up%20with%20stock%2C%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BMake%20the%20stock%20soar%2C%20and%20you'll%20be%20handsomely%20rewarded.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20thing%20boards%20of%20companies%20facing%20cost%20pressure%20want%20to%20do%20is%20cause%20their%20leaders%20to%20go%20looking.%20Cutting%20the%20compensation%20%E2%80%94%20making%20it%20not%20competitive%20with%20their%20peers%20%E2%80%94%20would%20do%20just%20that.%20It's%20something%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt's%20the%20image%2C%20though%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20with%20this%20purely%20economic%20discussion%2C%20however%2C%20is%20that%20it%20misses%20the%20entire%20point.%20These%20CEOs%20are%20supposed%20to%20be%20leaders.%20They're%20supposed%20to%20be%20setting%20a%20new%20course%2C%20and%20they're%20supposed%20to%20be%20models%20of%20behavior%20for%20the%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20company%20is%20going%20through%20pressure%2C%20and%20if%20things%20are%20so%20bad%20that%20people%20are%20losing%20their%20jobs%2C%20shouldn't%20the%20CEOs%20share%20the%20pain%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%20they%20should.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20have%2C%20under%20public%20pressure%2C%20made%20public%20commitments%20to%20do%20better.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffortune.com%2F2023%2F01%2F24%2Fgoogle-ceo-sundar-pichai-less-pay-like-jamie-dimon-and-tim-cook%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESundar%20Pichai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20committed%20a%20year%20ago%20to%20lower%20his%20pay%2C%20but%20as%20I%20already%20mentioned%2C%20his%20total%20compensation%20this%20past%20year%20was%20over%20%24200%20million.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F01%2F13%2Ftech%2Ftim-cook-apple-pay-cut%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ETim%20Cook%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20at%20Apple%20publicly%20requested%20his%20stock%20grant%20be%20cut%20in%20half%20%E2%80%94%20to%20%2440%20million.%20His%20base%20pay%20of%20%243%20million%20and%20bonus%20of%20%246%20million%20were%20unchanged.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20most%20don't.%20They'll%20make%20all%20the%20excuses%20above%2C%20justifying%20it%20to%20themselves%2C%20their%20boards%2C%20and%20their%20stockholders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20they'll%20turn%20to%20the%20company%20and%20make%20impassioned%20speeches%20about%20how%20hard%20this%20all%20is%2C%20how%20sad%20it%20is%20to%20see%20people%20go%2C%20and%20how%20they%20wish%20there%20were%20other%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20all%2C%20they'll%20talk%20about%20how%20we're%20all%20in%20this%20together%2C%20working%20for%20a%20stronger%20company%20tomorrow%2C%20then%20smile%20while%20they%20cash%20the%20checks%20and%20sell%20their%20stock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclwill.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EChris%20Williams%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20the%20former%20VP%20of%20HR%20at%20Microsoft.%20He%20is%20an%20executive-level%20advisor%20and%20consultant%20with%20over%2040%20years%20of%20experience%20leading%20and%20building%20teams.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexecutives-pay-cuts-dont-avoid-prevent-layoffs-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C