C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b9721cac2de4f17ee608c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20MIND%20diet%20focuses%20on%20eating%20patterns%20that%20protect%20your%20brain%20as%20you%20age%2C%20and%20you%20can%20get%20started%20with%20simple%20habits%20like%20adding%20more%20berries%20or%20greens%20to%20your%20meals.%3Cp%3EEkaterina%20Fedulyeva%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20MIND%20diet%20is%20designed%20to%20help%20prevent%20cognitive%20decline%20such%20as%20Alzheimer's%20disease%20as%20we%20age.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20similar%20to%20the%20Mediterranean%20diet%2C%20but%20recommends%20more%20specific%20foods%20like%20berries%20and%20greens.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EStart%20following%20the%20MIND%20diet%20with%20simple%20steps%20like%20adding%20a%20few%20servings%20of%20veggies%20each%20week.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20simple%2C%20Mediterranean-style%20eating%20plan%20may%20be%20one%20of%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-easy-simple-boost-longevity-live-longer-healthier-habits-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprotect%20your%20brain%20(and%20body)%20as%20you%20age%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20experts%20say%20you%20can%20start%20with%20easy%20additions%20to%20your%20grocery%20list%20and%20meal%20routine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20MIND%20diet%20%E2%80%94%20which%20stands%20for%20Mediterranean-DASH%20Intervention%20for%20Neurodegenerative%20Delay%20%E2%80%94%20incorporates%20elements%20of%20the%20notably%20healthy%20Mediterranean%20diet%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdash-diet-mistakes-to-avoid-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eheart-healthy%20DASH%20%3C%2Fa%3Ediet%2C%20along%20with%20foods%20linked%20to%20preventing%20cognitive%20decline%20as%20we%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20ranked%20one%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmediterrean-diet-healthiest-best-overall-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealthiest%20ways%20to%20eat%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20alongside%20the%20Mediterranean%20diet%2C%20and%20is%20a%20similarly%20non-restrictive%2C%20flexible%20eating%20plan.%20It%20was%20developed%20by%20a%20team%20of%20Harvard%20and%20Rush%20University%20researchers%20led%20by%20epidemiology%20professor%20Dr.%20Martha%20Clare%20Morris%2C%20who%20died%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20daughter%2C%20Laura%20Morris%2C%20is%20a%20chef%2C%20personal%20trainer%2C%20who%20has%20carried%20on%20her%20work%2C%20co-authoring%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheofficialminddiet.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Official%20MIND%20Diet%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20what%20separates%20it%20from%20other%20Mediterranean-style%20diets%20and%20similar%20health%20eating%20plans%20is%20that%20it%20offers%20more%20specific%20recommendations%20with%2010%20food%20groups%20to%20eat%20more%20of%2C%20which%20include%20leafy%20greens%2C%20other%20veggies%2C%20berries%2C%20olive%20oil%2C%20nuts%20and%20seeds%2C%20fish%2C%20chicken%2C%20whole%20grains%2C%20beans%2C%20and%20wine%20(in%20moderation).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recommendations%20are%20based%20on%20research%20about%20which%20foods%2C%20nutrients%2C%20and%20eating%20patterns%20can%20help%20prevent%20health%20issues%20like%20dementia%2C%20and%20are%20good%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flongevity-diet-food-list-cheap-easy-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoverall%20longevity%3C%2Fa%3E%20too%2C%20according%20to%20Morris.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20MIND%20diet%20focuses%20on%20helping%20you%20add%20more%20foods%20that%20benefit%20cognitive%20function%2C%20while%20gradually%20reducing%20foods%20linked%20to%20worse%20brain%20health%2C%20like%20red%20meat%20and%20sweets.%20What's%20distinct%20is%20that%20you%20aren't%20expected%20to%20cut%20out%20your%20favorite%20foods%20entirely%2C%20said%20Jennifer%20Ventrelle%2C%20a%20registered%20dietitian%20who%20co-authored%20the%20%26quot%3BThe%20Official%20MIND%20Diet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20diet%2C%20people%20probably%20expect%20a%20strict%20set%20of%20rules%20but%20we've%20written%20it%20so%20the%20idea%20is%20to%20start%20as%20you%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20you're%20new%20to%20healthy%20eating.%20or%20an%20established%20nutrition%20nerd%2C%20Ventrelle%20and%20Morris%20offer%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSfS-fti-wBXc3TwydO4t64nBEYn8qKFGI2Rpmrb4vRAB0CONA%2Fviewform%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eweek-to-week%20guide%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20how%20to%20follow%20the%20MIND%20diet%20without%20turning%20your%20life%20or%20kitchen%20upside%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20started%2C%20assess%20what%20you're%20currently%20eating%2C%20add%20a%20few%20extra%20servings%20of%20specific%20foods%20each%20week%2C%20and%20build%20up%20gradually%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmind-diet-for-beginners-common-mistakes-dietitian-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eavoid%20common%20beginner%20mistakes%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20doing%20too%20much%20too%20soon%2C%20or%20becoming%20restrictive%20with%20your%20eating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EStart%20by%20tracking%20what%20you're%20already%20eating%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20step%20of%20starting%20the%20MIND%20diet%20doesn't%20even%20require%20a%20trip%20to%20the%20grocery.%20Before%20you%20jump%20in%2C%20Ventrelle%20and%20Morris%20recommend%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Fbest-food-journals%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekeeping%20a%20log%20of%20what%20you%20eat%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20you%20can%20assess%20how%20your%20typical%20habits%20compare%20to%20the%20recommendations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20there%2C%20you%20can%20start%20reducing%20a%20little%20at%20a%20time%2C%20such%20as%20cutting%20out%20a%20few%20servings%20per%20week%20of%20processed%20or%20fried%20food%2C%20and%20gradually%20adding%20more%20recommended%20foods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20know%20what%20to%20change%20if%20you%20don't%20know%20what%20the%20problem%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20Morris%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdd%20brain-healthy%20foods%20like%20berries%20and%20greens%20to%20what%20you're%20already%20eating%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20distinct%20feature%20of%20the%20MIND%20diet%20is%20that%20instead%20of%20banning%20foods%20or%20focusing%20on%20what%20you%20can't%20eat%2C%20it%20emphasizes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-lose-weight-by-eating-more-according-to-dietitians-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadding%20foods%20to%20improve%20your%20health%20(and%20even%20lose%20weight%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20if%20that's%20a%20goal).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20you%20can%20incorporate%20the%20MIND%20diet%20into%20your%20current%20habits%20by%20building%20on%20meals%20and%20snacks%20you%20typically%20enjoy%2C%20like%20adding%20a%20handful%20of%20berries%20to%20your%20morning%20yogurt%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnutrition-hack-make-green-smoothies-healthier-recipes-milk-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblending%20some%20greens%20into%20a%20shake%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20meant%20to%20say%20you%20can%20only%20eat%20the%2010%20foods%20on%20the%20list%20and%20stay%20away%20from%20the%20foods%20on%20the%20list%20to%20limit%2C%26quot%3B%20Ventrelle%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFocus%20on%20a%20few%20servings%20of%20healthy%20foods%20per%20week%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20MIND%20diet%20is%20relatively%20simple%2C%20trying%20to%20change%20everything%20at%20once%20can%20be%20overwhelming.%20Ventrelle%20said%20she%20still%20uses%20simple%20tools%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheofficialminddiet.com%2Ftools%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMIND%20diet%20tracker%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20home%20to%20help%20her%20improve%20over%20time.%20Begin%20with%20a%20small%20shift%20in%20a%20single%20category%20at%20a%20time%2C%20such%20as%20eating%20fewer%20servings%20of%20red%20meat%20or%20more%20helpings%20of%20berries.%20That%20way%2C%20you%20can%20build%20progress%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPick%20one%20or%20two%20things%20to%20change%2C%20and%20find%20very%20specific%20and%20measurable%20ways%20to%20change.%20Give%20yourself%20some%20grace%2C%26quot%3B%20Morris%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20wait%20%E2%80%94%20right%20now%20is%20the%20best%20time%20to%20start%20the%20MIND%20diet%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20MIND%20diet%20can%20be%20beneficial%20at%20just%20about%20any%20age%2C%20since%20brain%20changes%20can%20begin%20as%20early%20as%20your%2030s%2C%20according%20to%20Morris.%20And%20while%20the%20diet%20can't%20reverse%20Alzheimer's%20disease%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcontent.iospress.com%2Farticles%2Fjournal-of-alzheimers-disease%2Fjad210107%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eevidence%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggests%20it%20may%20be%20protective%20in%20older%20adults%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20right%20time.%20It's%20never%20too%20early%20or%20too%20late%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20worry%20about%20being%20perfect%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20you%20panic%20about%20checking%20off%20every%20box%20on%20the%20MIND%20diet%20guide%2C%20know%20that%20it%20isn't%20an%20all-or-nothing%20endeavor.%20Research%20suggests%20the%20benefits%20of%20the%20MIND%20diet%20can%20happen%20on%20a%20spectrum%20so%20making%20some%20small%20changes%20can%20protect%20your%20brain%20even%20if%20you%20don't%20manage%20to%20get%20exactly%20the%20right%20servings%20of%20every%20food%20each%20week