target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20advisor%20role%20last%20summer%20after%20stints%20in%20other%20positions%2C%20including%20on%20the%20National%20Security%20Council.%20Since%20then%2C%20President%20Biden%20has%20issued%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2023%2F10%2F30%2Ffact-sheet-president-biden-issues-executive-order-on-safe-secure-and-trustworthy-artificial-intelligence%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EExecutive%20Order%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20AI%2C%20demanding%2C%20in%20part%2C%20greater%20transparency%20from%20companies%20developing%20powerful%20AI%20tools%20and%20outlining%20actions%20for%20various%20government%20agencies%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20three%20months%20since%20the%20executive%20order%20was%20issued%2C%20the%20White%20House%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2024%2F01%2F29%2Ffact-sheet-biden-harris-administration-announces-key-ai-actions-following-president-bidens-landmark-executive-order%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emade%20progress%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20a%20number%20of%20the%20directives.%20However%2C%20AI%20has%20evolved%20rapidly%20in%20that%20time%2C%20sometimes%20in%20troubling%20ways%2C%20like%20making%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbytedance-ai-model-speak-in-another-persons-voice-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecreation%20of%20deepfakes%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20easier%20than%20ever.%20Generative%20AI%20was%20even%20used%20to%20fake%20a%20robocall%20impersonating%20President%20Biden%20that%20urged%20people%20not%20to%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuchanan%20admitted%20that%20the%20White%20House's%20power%20to%20set%20standards%20for%20AI%20technology%20is%20very%20limited.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20not%20something%20we%20have%20the%20legal%20authority%20to%20do%20by%20executive%20action%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20However%2C%20he%20alluded%20to%20future%20regulation%20around%20AI%2C%20noting%20that%20Biden%20is%20set%20to%20have%20%26quot%3Blegislative%20conversations%20here%20in%20the%20month%20ahead.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomething%20else%20that%20has%20developed%20since%20the%20executive%20order%20came%20out%20is%20the%20debate%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-copyright-protect-ai-model-argues-against-law-everyone-else-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecopyright%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20AI.%20The%20US%20Copyright%20Office%20last%20year%20opened%20a%20public%20comment%20period%20as%20it%20considers%20new%20rules%20around%20generative%20AI%20and%20the%20training%20of%20large%20language%20models%2C%20which%20require%20huge%20amounts%20of%20online%20content.%20The%20likes%20of%20Meta%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20OpenAI%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20others%20use%20mountains%20of%20copyrighted%20content%20for%20free%20in%20their%20model%20training%2C%20but%20claim%20that's%20necessary%20for%20the%20technology%20to%20make%20sense%20financially.%20Copyright%20holders%20largely%20disagree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuchanan%20said%20the%20White%20House's%20doesn't%20have%20an%20official%20stance%20on%20this.%20But%20its%20general%20priority%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Bhave%20an%20innovative%20AI%20ecosystem%26quot%3B%20while%20ensuring%20%26quot%3Bthe%20people%20who%20create%20meaningful%20content%20are%20appropriately%20compensated%20for%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFor%20BI's%20complete%20conversation%20with%20Buchanan%2C%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity%2C%20see%20below%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20alluded%20a%20minute%20ago%20to%20it%20being%20kind%20of%20crazy%2C%20but%20has%20this%20AI%20specific%20role%20been%20very%20intense%20compared%20to%20your%20previous%20roles%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Security%20Council%20is%20pretty%20intense%2C%20too.%20I%20think%20probably%20one%20thing%20that's%20the%20case%20is%20we've%20been%20working%20as%20an%20administration%20on%20AI%20basically%20since%20we%20started%20here%20in%202021%2C%20but%20the%20public%20attention%20has%20only%20increased%2C%20and%20that%20itself%20creates%20more%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDid%20the%20explosion%20in%20public%20awareness%20surprise%20you%20when%20it%20happened%3F%20I%20assume%20it's%20post%20ChatGPT%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20I%20was%20probably%20less%20surprised%20than%20others%20because%20I%20was%20so%20familiar%20with%20the%20technology%20and%20what%20it%20could%20do.%20And%20then%20the%20senior%20leadership%20here%20understood%20the%20benefits%20and%20risks%20of%20AI%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20there%20any%20use%20cases%20of%20generative%20AI%20that%20you%20find%20particularly%20helpful%2C%20useful%2C%20hopeful%3F%20Where%20you%20looked%20at%20the%20tech%20and%20thought%2C%20wow%2C%20this%20is%20great.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYeah%2C%20there's%20three%20levels%20here.%20You%20can%20look%20at%20the%20individual%20level%2C%20then%20you%20can%20look%20at%20the%20government-wide%20use%20level%2C%20and%20then%20you%20could%20look%20at%20big%20picture%20societal%20priorities.%20On%20an%20individual%20level%2C%20I%20don't%20really%20use%20generative%20AI%20much%20at%20all.%20Mostly%20because%20I%20sit%20in%20the%20government%20and%20spend%20most%20of%20my%20time%20working%20in%20the%20government%2C%20and%20we%20don't%2C%20to%20my%20knowledge%2C%20we%20don't%20have%20particularly%20developed%20policies%20and%20processes%20for%20this.%20And%20also%20because%20a%20huge%20portion%20of%20my%20job%20is%20meetings%20and%20email.%20So%20there's%20not%20a%20ton%20of%20reason%20to%20use%20it%20here%2C%20but%20I'm%20not%20sure%20where%20it%20would%20be%20appropriate%20or%20inappropriate%20to%20do%20so.%20So%20I'm%20not%20a%20particularly%20compelling%20use%20case%20right%20now%2C%20just%20given%20that%20most%20of%20my%20job%20is%20talking%20to%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYeah%2C%20okay.%20There's%20not%20an%20avatar%20Ben%20taking%20your%20meetings%20yet%2C%20is%20what%20you're%20saying.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExactly.%20Sign%20me%20up%20for%20that%20though.%20Second%2C%20is%20what%20are%20the%20appropriate%20federal%20government%20uses%20of%20this%20technology%3F%20And%20here%20I%20think%20there's%20actually%20a%20fair%20amount%2C%20and%20section%2010%20of%20the%20executive%20order%20is%20pretty%20clear%20at%20saying%20be%20responsible%2C%20but%20make%20sure%20we're%20innovating%20here.%20The%20Office%20of%20Management%20and%20Budget%20is%20taking%20the%20lead%20here%2C%20and%20this%20governs%20how%20agencies%20outside%20of%20a%20national%20security%20context%20should%20use%20AI.%20So%20this%20is%20the%20case%20where%20we%20talk%20about%20what%20are%20the%20places%20where%20it's%20pretty%20high%20risk%20to%20use%20AI%2C%20and%20we%20need%20to%20really%20be%20careful%20that%20we're%20respecting%20human%20rights%20and%20the%20like%2C%20and%20what%20are%20the%20cases%20that%20it's%20much%20lower%20risk%20and%20we%20should%20probably%20be%20leading%20pretty%20aggressively%20and%20using%20AI%20to%20deliver%20better%20services%20for%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20I%20don't%20know%20if%20you're%20interested%20in%20the%20last%20question%2C%20which%20is%20big%20picture%2C%20what%20are%20some%20of%20those%20promising%20use%20cases%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYeah%2C%20totally.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20that%20I'm%20really%20excited%20about%20are%20AI%20for%20science%20and%20generative%20AI%2C%20but%20also%20more%20generally%20AI%20systems%20in%20biology%20and%20healthcare.%20Scientific%20discovery%20is%20a%20priority%20for%20the%20President%20and%20I%20think%20we're%20all%20united%20here%20and%20recognizing%20the%20potential%20for%20the%20technology%20in%20that%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHas%20anything%20crossed%20to%20your%20desk%20or%20come%20up%20in%20any%20meetings%20that%20you%20had%20over%20the%20past%20year%20where%20you%20were%20just%20like%2C%20oh%20no%2C%20this%20could%20be%20potentially%20bad%20and%20you%20really%20wanted%20to%20get%20ahead%20of%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure.%20I%20think%20one%20example%20here%20again%2C%20and%20it%20illustrates%20the%20dual%20nature%20of%20a%20lot%20of%20AI%20is%20again%2C%20AI%20for%20science%20and%20in%20particular%20AI%20for%20biology.%20Our%20view%20is%20the%20more%20we%20can%20manage%20those%20risks%2C%20the%20more%20we'll%20be%20able%20to%20harness%20the%20benefits.%20In%20the%20same%20way%20that%20in%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20railroad%2C%20it%20was%20the%20trains%20that%20had%20brakes%20and%20safety%20procedures%20that%20could%20go%20much%20faster%20than%20the%20trains%20that%20didn't.%20I%20think%20we%20want%20to%20create%20an%20ecosystem%20here%20at%20the%20intersection%20of%20AI%20and%20biology%2C%20but%20also%20more%20generally%20at%20the%20intersection%20of%20AI%20and%20society%2C%20where%20we've%20got%20the%20right%20procedures%20in%20place%20so%20that%20we%20can%20go%20as%20fast%20as%20we%20can%20safely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20big%20conversation%20about%20improper%20uses%20of%20AI%20lately%20has%20been%20around%20deepFakes%2C%20which%20people%20have%20been%20talking%20about%20for%20years.%20But%20do%20you%20agree%20with%20the%20developing%20wisdom%20that%20the%20power%20behind%20these%20generative%20AI%20tools%20now%20make%20deepfakes%20so%20much%20easier%20to%20create%3F%20You%20need%20little%20to%20no%20technical%20know-how%20now%20to%20do%20something%20like%20fake%20President%20Biden's%20voice%2C%20et%20cetera.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYeah%2C%20I%20don't%20know%20exactly%20where%20it's%20at%2C%20is%20it%20little%20or%20no%20know-how.%20But%20yeah%2C%20I%20think%20as%20a%20general%20view%2C%20we%20recognize%20that%20increasingly%20powerful%20technology%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20do%20things%20like%20clone%20voices%20or%20fake%20videos.%20And%20we%20want%20to%20not%20inhibit%20the%20creativity%20that%20could%20come%20from%20having%20more%20powerful%20tools%2C%20while%20also%20making%20sure%20we%20manage%20some%20of%20the%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20two%20places%20I'd%20point%20to%20here%20where%20we've%20acted%20on%20this%20one%2C%20the%20President%20received%20commitments%20from%20the%2015%20leading%20AI%20companies%20in%20the%20United%20States%20over%20the%20summer%20of%202023%2C%20and%20that%20included%20a%20commitment%20to%20build%20and%20deploy%20watermarking%20systems%2C%20especially%20that%20when%20their%20AI%20tools%20generate%20content%2C%20there's%20a%20watermark%20built%20into%20it.%20This%20is%20a%20tricky%20technical%20problem%20and%20one%20that's%20going%20to%20take%20a%20long%20time%20to%2C%20not%20to%20solve%20the%20watermarking%20question%2C%20but%20solve%20the%20question%20of%20how%20do%20you%20surface%20that%20information%20to%20a%20user%20in%20a%20meaningful%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20second%2C%20in%20the%20executive%20order%2C%20we%20stand%20up%20the%20AI%20Safety%20Institute%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Commerce.%20It%20has%20a%20number%20of%20jobs%2C%20but%20one%20is%20to%20set%20standards%20for%20watermarking%20content%2C%20providence%2C%20to%20help%20address%20this.%20There's%20another%20part%2C%20we're%20trying%20to%20explore%20this%2C%20it's%20a%20longer%20process%2C%20but%20essentially%20cryptographically%20verifying%20our%20own%20communication%20so%20that%20when%20people%20see%20a%20video%20of%20the%20President%20on%20whitehouse.gov%2C%20they%20know%20this%20is%20a%20real%20video%20of%20the%20president%20and%20there's%20some%20signature%20in%20there%20that%20does%20that.%20So%20I%20think%20this%20is%20a%20case%20where%20we%20recognize%20the%20potential%20for%20harm.%20We're%20trying%20to%20get%20ahead%20of%20it%2C%20and%20we've%20been%20working%20on%20this%20for%20quite%20a%20while.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20what%20do%20you%20say%20to%20criticism%20of%20the%20executive%20order%3F%20That%20it's%20a%20little%20bit%20soft%2C%20it's%20a%20lot%20of%20suggestions%2C%20even%20proposals%20for%20proposals%2C%20about%20how%20this%20stuff%20should%20happen%20and%20when.%20And%20now%20we're%20in%20an%20election%20year.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20certainly%20I%20get%20criticism%20that%20the%20executive%20order%20is%20too%20aggressive%20sometimes.%20I%20don't%20know%20that%20we've%20gotten%20a%20ton%20of%20criticism%20that%20it's%20too%20soft%2C%20but%20maybe%20folks%20think%20that.%20I%20think%20in%20the%20case%20of%20deepfakes%2C%20it%20is%20a%20question%20of%20what%20is%20the%20appropriate%20role%20for%20government%20here%2C%20bearing%20in%20mind%20that%20there%20are%20free%20speech%20rights%20and%20indeed%20campaign%20and%20election%20rights%20and%20all%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20we%20would%20probably%20do%20is%20not%20with%20reference%20to%20elections%20in%20particular%2C%20but%20more%20generally%2C%20try%20to%20create%20an%20environment%20in%20which%20folks%20who%20consume%20content%20generated%20by%20AI%20know%20that%20it's%20been%20generated%20by%20AI.%20And%20we've%20done%20that%20through%20working%20with%20the%20companies%20and%20also%20through%20the%20process%20of%20setting%20standards%20more%20generally%20for%20the%20industry.%20I%20don't%20know%20that%20the%20standards%20are%20legally%20compelling%2C%20right%3F%20I%20don't%20know%20that%20we%20have%20legal%20authority%2C%20certainly%20not%20under%20the%20executive%20order%2C%20to%20say%20these%20are%20the%20standards%20that%20every%20AI%20provider%20in%20the%20United%20States%20needs%20to%20adhere%20to%20for%20generating%20content.%20That%20is%20not%20something%20we%20have%20the%20legal%20authority%20to%20do%20by%20executive%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOkay%2C%20about%20that.%20How%20can%20you%20actually%20at%20all%20compel%20these%20companies%20to%20report%20developmental%20work%2C%20report%20safety%20results%20to%20you%3F%20And%20then%20what%20happens%20if%20they%20do%20and%20something%20seems%20problematic%20to%20Commerce%3F%20What%20is%20the%20process%20then%20of%20dealing%20with%20that%2C%20if%20there%20is%20a%20problem%20that's%20flagged%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20the%20reporting%20of%20safety%20results%20is%20a%20different%20authority%20than%20the%20watermarking%20discussion.%20This%20is%20down%20to%20the%20minutiae%20here%2C%20but%20the%20watermarking%20discussion%20is%20NIST%20essentially%20setting%20voluntary%20standards%20and%20good%20practices%20for%20'this%20is%20what%20it%20should%20look%20like%20to%20watermark%20your%20content.'%20Now%2C%20the%20companies%20have%20already%20said%20they%20are%20going%20to%20watermark%20their%20content%20as%20part%20of%20the%20voluntary%20commitments.%20So%20hopefully%20there's%20some%20kind%20of%20marriage%20that%20can%20happen%20of%20good%20standards%20set%20collaboratively%20with%20commitments%20that%20companies%20made%2C%20and%20we%20don't%20need%20any%20legal%20authority%20to%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOkay.%20Separate%20from%20all%20of%20that%20is%2C%20as%20they're%20building%20an%20extremely%20capable%20AI%20system%2C%20what%20safety%20obligations%20do%20they%20have%3F%20And%20here%20we%20do%20have%20an%20authority%20in%20play%20called%20the%20Defense%20Production%20Act%2C%20which%20has%20survey%20authority%2C%20where%20we%20can%20essentially%20go%20to%20the%20companies%20and%20say%2C%20we%20are%20surveying%20you%20for%20your%20information%20about%20the%20system%20you%20are%20building.%20And%20this%20authority%20dates%20from%201953.%20This%20has%20been%20used%20in%20tons%20of%20contexts%20in%20different%20industries%20to%20understand%20essentially%20what%20the%20state%20of%20play%20is%20in%20those%20industries.%20And%20that%20is%20an%20authority%20that%20is%20legally%20backed.%20They're%20compelled%20to%20turn%20that%20information%20over%2C%20whereas%20the%20watermarking%20content%20providence%20is%20not%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOkay.%20And%20so%20you've%20delivered%20those%20surveys%2C%20I%20assume%2C%20to%20all%2015%20companies%20then%2C%20just%20to%20ensure%20that%20they%20are%20compelled%20to%20give%20you%20this%20information%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes.%20The%20Department%20of%20Commerce%20handles%20it.%20The%20surveys%20are%20out.%20I%20don't%20know%20exactly%20who%20got%20them%20or%20how%20many%20companies.%20So%20I%20would%20defer%20to%20Commerce%20on%20how%20they%20structured%20who%20got%20them.%20But%20yes%2C%20the%20surveys%20are%20out.%20It%20was%20a%2090-day%20deliverable%20and%20we%20met%20it%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%20is%20good%20minutiae%2C%20by%20the%20way.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20talking%2C%20for%20better%20or%20for%20worse%2C%20to%20the%20right%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20two%20more%20things%20since%20we're%20running%20out%20of%20time%3A%20The%20AI%20and%20copyright%20debate%20that's%20going%20on%20and%20then%20also%20regulatory%20action.%20Do%20you%20or%20the%20White%20House%20have%20thoughts%20on%20where%20AI%20training%20falls%20in%20copyright%20law%3F%20Is%20it%20transformative%20fair%20use%3F%20And%20then%2C%20when%20you%20look%20at%20something%20like%20the%20EU%20AI%20Act%2C%20do%20you%20foresee%20the%20US%20ever%20going%20to%20that%20length%2C%20really%20enacting%20national%2C%20federal%20regulation%20around%20AI%3F%20Or%20is%20it%20more%20a%20kind%20of%20wait%20and%20see%20if%20it%20needs%20to%20happen%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOkay%2C%20let's%20go%20in%20order.%20So%20the%20Copyright%20Office%2C%20as%20you%20probably%20know%2C%20is%20actually%20independent%20of%20the%20executive%20branch.%20So%20we%20don't%20really%20direct%20them%2C%20which%20is%20probably%20how%20it%20should%20be.%20So%20I%20think%20it's%20fair%20to%20say%20I%20don't%20have%20strong%20views%20here%20on%20that%20particularly%20matter.%20There's%20also%20the%20Patent%20and%20Trademark%20Office%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Commerce.%20We've%20basically%20gone%20to%20those%20agencies%20and%20asked%20for%20insights%2C%20but%20there's%20not%20an%20administration%20position%20on%20that%20yet%20in%20the%20way%20that%20there%20is%20in%20other%20areas%2C%20except%20to%20say%20that%20our%20general%20priorities%20are%20making%20sure%20that%20we%20have%20an%20innovative%20AI%20ecosystem%20and%20making%20sure%20the%20people%20who%20create%20meaningful%20content%20are%20appropriately%20compensated%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOkay.%20On%20the%20regulatory%20side%2C%20I%20think%20there's%20basically%20two%20pieces%20here.%20The%20first%20is%20what%20is%20the%20EU%20doing%3F%20And%20there's%20a%20fair%20amount%20in%20flux%20because%20they've%20pushed%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20authority%20and%20details%20to%20the%20office%20that%20they're%20creating.%20We've%20had%20very%20productive%20conversations%20with%20them%20and%20expect%20to%20continue%20productive%20conversations%20with%20them.%20And%20that'll%20be%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20what%20we%20are%20doing%2C%20the%20President%20invited%20the%20four%20senators%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bgang%20of%20four%2C%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20Oval%20Office%20the%20day%20after%20he%20signed%20the%20executive%20order.%20They%20had%20a%20good%20conversation%20there%20about%20broader%20legislative%20frameworks.%20Senator%20Schumer%20and%20that%20team%20has%20had%20Insight%20Forums%20on%20AI%20and%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20feedback%20basically%20from%20all-comers.%20I%20think%20we%20will%20have%20legislative%20conversations%20here%20in%20the%20month%20ahead.%20As%20you%20also%20know%2C%20Congress%20has%20got%20a%20lot%20going%20on%20right%20now%2C%20so%20I%20wouldn't%20want%20to%20place%20bets%20on%20timing%20or%20anything%20like%20that.%20But%20I%20think%20it's%20fair%20to%20say%20that%20we%20recognize%20we've%20done%20a%20lot%20with%20executive%20authority%2C%20and%20there's%20some%20things%20you%20can't%20do%20through%20executive%20authority%20that%20we%20might%20want%20to%20do%2C%20and%20we'll%20have%20that%20conversation%20with%20the%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-house-ai-copyright-debate-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706781601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bab4cd7a3d271488765f4d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-house-ai-copyright-debate-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22President%20Biden's%20AI%20advisor%20Ben%20Buchanan%20talks%20to%20Business%20Insider%20about%20the%20White%20House's%20positions%20on%20this%20new%20technology.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22khays%40insider.com%20(Kali%20Hays)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-house-ai-copyright-debate-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Top%20workers%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20want%20to%20quit%20when%20companies%20have%20strict%20return-to-office%20mandates%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Commuters%20arrive%20on%20Wall%20Street%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bac77743bb77284ba252e1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStrict%20return-to-office%20mandates%20can%20make%20top%20workers%20want%20to%20leave.%3Cp%3EMark%20Lennihan%2FAssociated%20Press%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETop%20workers%20are%2016%25%20less%20likely%20to%20want%20to%20stay%20in%20a%20job%20when%20an%20employer%20is%20strict%20on%20office%20days.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-workers-getting-boot-again-rto-wayfair-tech-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn-to-office%20mandate%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20also%20put%20off%20workers%20in%20general%2C%20according%20to%20Gartner.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20research%20firm%20said%20women%2C%20millennials%20are%20likelier%20to%20want%20to%20leave%20jobs%20with%20strict%20RTO%20rules.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20a%20star%20at%20work%20but%20your%20boss%20makes%20you%20head%20into%20the%20office%2C%20you're%20more%20likely%20to%20start%20hunting%20for%20a%20new%20gig.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gartner.com%2Fen%2Fnewsroom%2Fpress-releases%2F2024-01-30-gartner-hr-research-finds-high-performers-women-millennials-are-greatest-flight-risks%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGartner%3C%2Fa%3E%20indicates%20that%20high-performing%20workers%20are%2016%25%20less%20inclined%20to%20stay%20in%20their%20jobs%20when%20employers%20roll%20out%20strict%20return-to-office%20mandates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGartner%20defined%20the%20high-performers%20as%20those%20advancing%20more%20quickly%20in%20their%20career%20than%20their%20peers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20from%20a%20survey%20of%20nearly%202%2C100%20white-collar%20workers%20come%20as%20major%20employers%2C%20from%20banks%20to%20tech%20companies%2C%20push%20their%20people%20to%20head%20to%20the%20office.%20UPS%20on%20Tuesday%20announced%20big%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fups-layoffs-ceo-soft-demand-high-labor-costs-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecuts%20to%20its%20executive%20ranks%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20said%20it%20would%20require%20those%20remaining%20to%20be%20in%20five%20days%20a%20week.%20Other%20major%20companies%20have%20said%20employees%20who%20skip%20their%20commutes%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frto-return-to-office-mandate-be-fired-amazon-meta-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epay%20a%20price%20in%20their%20reviews%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cubicle%20callback%20also%20comes%20amid%20mixed%20signals%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fare-remote-jobs-more-productive-work-life-balance-return-office-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehow%20important%20it%20is%20to%20always%20be%20in%20the%20office%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20recent%20study%20suggested%20companies%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-mandates-remote-work-stock-returns-productivity-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Erequire%20time%20in%20the%20office%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20actually%20aren't%20more%20profitable%20or%20productive.%20But%20the%20effect%20of%20rigid%20RTO%20requests%20isn't%20necessarily%20limited%20to%20what%20shows%20up%20on%20a%20balance%20sheet%2C%20Caitlin%20Duffy%2C%20a%20research%20director%20in%20the%20Gartner%20HR%20practice%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BReturn-to-office%20mandates%20are%20a%20very%20risky%20proposition.%20They%20may%20be%20more%20about%20what%20leaders%20want%20than%20what%20really%20benefits%20employees%2C%20both%20personally%20and%20professionally%2C%26quot%3B%20Duffy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGartner's%20survey%2C%20conducted%20from%20May%20through%20June%202023%2C%20showed%20that%20employees%2C%20in%20general%2C%20were%208%25%20less%20likely%20to%20want%20to%20stick%20around%20when%20bosses%20put%20in%20an%20inflexible%20RTO%20mandate.%20Among%20women%2C%2011%25%20were%20less%20likely%20to%20want%20to%20stay.%20That's%20partly%20because%20women%20often%20value%20flexibility%20and%20might%20feel%20they%20face%20less%20bias%20when%20they're%20not%20in%20the%20office%2C%20according%20to%20the%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20among%20millennials%2C%20who%20Gartner%20said%20were%20most%20likely%20to%20have%20to%20juggle%20caregiving%20duties%2C%20tight%20rules%20about%20being%20in%20the%20office%20made%20them%2010%25%20less%20likely%20to%20want%20to%20stay%20at%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20wanting%20to%20quit%20and%20leaving%20are%20two%20different%20things.%20Still%2C%20Duffy%20said%2C%20having%20unhappy%20workers%20stick%20around%20can%20be%20its%20own%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20going%20to%20get%20the%20best%20out%20of%20those%20employees%20if%20they're%20people%20who%20are%20looking%20to%20leave%20at%20the%20next%20possible%20opportunity%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuffy%20said%20there's%20a%20benefit%20to%20bringing%20workers%20together.%20The%20survey%20showed%20employee%20engagement%20rose%20for%20most%20workers%2C%20particularly%20Gen%20Zers%2C%20when%20they%20were%20required%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office.%C2%A0But%2C%20she%20said%2C%20it%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20buy%20into%20a%20trip%20to%20the%20office%20when%20they%20understand%20why%20going%20in%20would%20be%20helpful%20and%20when%20they've%20had%20a%20hand%20in%20crafting%20the%20office%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20going%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20more%20successful%20than%20an%20arbitrary%20requirement%2C%26quot%3B%20Duffy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaking%20attendance%20at%20the%20office%20can%20also%20rankle%20high-performing%20employees%2C%20she%20said%2C%20because%20they're%20often%20stretched%20and%20need%20autonomy%20to%20work%20in%20a%20way%20that's%20best%20for%20them.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20their%20performance%2C%20they%20should%20be%20trusted%20to%20structure%20their%20workdays%20and%20have%20flexibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20leaders%20often%20get%20wrong%20is%20thinking%20that%20employees%20are%20just%20trying%20to%20do%20less%20work%20or%20get%20more%20out%20of%20their%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20Duffy%20said.%20%26quot%3BEmployees%20want%20to%20perform%20well%2C%20and%20they%20want%20to%20be%20trusted%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20they%20know%20their%20work%20best.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%2