20ethnic%20armed%20organisations%20launched%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthediplomat.com%2F2023%2F11%2Foperation-1027-is-changing-myanmars-frontier-geographies-is-india-ready%2F%5C%22%3Ecoordinated%20offensives%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0against%20junta%20targets%20in%20northern%20Myanmar%2C%20the%20military%20has%20struggled%20to%20keep%20its%20head%20above%20the%20water.%20It%20has%20lost%20large%20swathes%20of%20territory%20to%20revolutionary%20forces.%20Entire%20battalions%20have%20surrendered%20without%20a%20fight%2C%20the%20latest%20one%20being%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irrawaddy.com%2Fnews%2Fburma%2Fmyanmar-junta-infantry-battalion-surrenders-to-aa-in-rakhine-state.html%5C%22%3ERakhine%20State%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Even%20its%20neutral%20partners%20and%20long-time%20allies%2C%20such%20as%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irrawaddy.com%2Fnews%2Fburma%2Fethnic-pa-o-group-exits-myanmar-peace-talks-formally-joins-war-against-dictatorship.html%5C%22%3Epro-talks%20ethnic%20armed%20groups%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20subordinate%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frontiermyanmar.net%2Fen%2Fwhats-at-stake-as-the-kayin-bgf-seeks-independence%2F%5C%22%3Eborder%20militias%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20are%20abandoning%20the%20sinking%20ship%20that%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9CState%20Administration%20Council%E2%80%9D.%20Most%20of%20all%2C%20the%20top%20boss%20himself%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frontiermyanmar.net%2Fen%2Fworst-leader-militarys-winter-of-discontent%2F%5C%22%3Efacing%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0rising%20internal%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20to%20forget%20the%20unfathomable%20human%20costs%20of%20the%20putsch%3A%20more%20than%204%2C400%20killed%2C%2025%2C000%20arrested%2C%20and%202.6%20million%20internally%20displaced%2C%20all%20since%20February%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20these%2C%20the%20government%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20India%20continues%20to%20formally%20engage%20with%20(only)%20the%20junta.%20It%20has%20had%20conversations%20with%20pro-democracy%20entities%20since%20the%20coup%2C%20but%20these%20have%20been%20no%20more%20than%20informal%2C%20below-the-radar%2C%20or%20at%20times%2C%20purely%20tactical%2C%20engagements%20that%20haven%E2%80%99t%20resulted%20in%20any%20policy%20shift%20at%20the%20highest%20levels%20of%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20could%20argue%20that%20India%20continues%20to%20formally%20engage%20the%20junta%20because%20of%20its%20entrenched%20geopolitical%20interests%20in%20Myanmar.%20Three%20key%20objectives%20become%20salient%20here%3A%20securing%20and%20stabilising%20the%20India-Myanmar%20border%2C%20maintaining%20and%20strengthening%20economic%20ties%2C%20and%20balancing%20the%20Chinese%20presence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20these%20are%20inadequate%20in%20explaining%20why%20New%20Delhi%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20yet%20formalised%20its%20engagement%20with%20the%20democratic%20forces%20in%20Myanmar.%20In%20fact%2C%20one%20could%20even%20argue%20that%20if%20it%20was%20really%20about%20fulfilling%20key%20strategic%20objectives%20and%20protecting%20its%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20interests%E2%80%9D%2C%20India%20should%20have%20already%20engaged%20the%20democratic%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20three%20deeper%20structural%20and%20ideological%20factors%20that%20explain%20the%20orthodox%2C%20pro-junta%20posture%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPath%20dependency%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%2C%20the%20Indian%20political%20and%20security%20establishments%20are%20path%20dependent%20on%20working%20with%20the%20Myanmar%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20early%201990s%2C%20New%20Delhi%2C%20guided%20by%20a%20strictly%20realpolitik%20logic%2C%20has%20abidingly%20worked%20with%20successive%20military%20regimes%20in%20the%20country.%20The%20end%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%20and%20the%20opening%20up%20of%20the%20Indian%20economy%20in%20quick%20succession%20created%20an%20overwhelming%20incentive%20within%20the%20Indian%20foreign%20policy%20system%20to%20prioritise%20economic%20growth%20and%20strategic%20outreach%20over%20idealism.%20The%20result%20was%20a%20cold%2C%20arithmetic%20mantra%20%E2%80%93%20work%20with%20whoever%20is%20in%20power%20in%20the%20Burmese%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20path%20dependency%20became%20even%20stronger%20in%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20as%20the%20Modi%20government%20fortified%20relations%20with%20the%20Myanmar%20military.%20Importantly%2C%20it%20did%20so%20despite%20the%20democratic%20transition%20next%20door%2C%20which%20brought%20Aung%20San%20Suu%20Kyi%20to%20power%20in%20a%20free-and-fair%20election.%20While%20New%20Delhi%20embraced%20her%20administration%20with%20open%20arms%2C%20its%20continued%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20military%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20going%20anywhere%20anytime%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20there%20was%20a%20surge%20in%20bilateral%20activity%20between%20the%20defence%20establishments%20in%20New%20Delhi%20and%20Naypyitaw%20after%202015.%20High-profile%20mutual%20visits%20of%20senior%20def-sec%20officials%2C%20joint%20counterinsurgency%20operations%20along%20the%20border%2C%20military%20training%20exercises%2C%20sale%20of%20heavy%20military%20hardware%20(such%20as%20torpedoes%20and%20submarines)%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Modi%20government%20really%20gave%20it%20all%20to%20invest%20in%20Min%20Aung%20Hlaing%E2%80%99s%20military.%20All%20of%20this%20was%20designed%20to%20fortify%20the%20Indian%20presence%20at%20China%E2%80%99s%20doorsteps%20and%20create%20strategic%20depth%20in%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20Delhi%20has%20found%20it%20difficult%20to%20break%20out%20of%20this%20path%20dependency%20%E2%80%93%20some%20would%20say%2C%20overreliance%20%E2%80%93%20after%20the%202021%20coup.%20It%20is%20predisposed%20to%20believing%20that%20the%20military%20remains%20a%20formidable%20political%20force%20in%20Myanmar%20that%20is%20facing%20serious%20challenges%2C%20but%20will%20eventually%20%E2%80%9Cstabilise%E2%80%9D%20the%20country%20like%20it%20has%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Myanmar%2C%20there%20is%20another%20legacy%20impulse%20to%20which%20India%20remains%20hostage%3A%20working%20with%20a%20prominent%20civilian%20leader.%20New%20Delhi%20was%20very%20much%20taken%20in%20by%20Suu%20Kyi%20because%20of%20her%20towering%20global%20image%2C%20undisputed%20dominance%20in%20domestic%20politics%2C%20and%20past%20connections%20with%20India.%20The%202021%20coup%20and%20the%20multi-ethnic%20revolution%20that%20came%20in%20its%20wake%20pushed%20her%20into%20oblivion.%20New%20Delhi%20barely%20recognises%20the%20new%20faces%20populating%20the%20current%20pro-democracy%20spectrum%2C%20including%20the%20senior%20leadership%20of%20the%20National%20Unity%20Government%20(NUG).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20suggestions%20made%20to%20New%20Delhi%20on%20talking%20to%20the%20NUG%20are%20often%20returned%20with%20a%20cross-question%3A%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ewhom%20should%20we%20talk%20to%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20different%20matter%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20done%20enough%20to%20familiarise%20itself%20with%20the%20new%20generation%20of%20leaders%2C%20many%20of%20them%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Z%2C%20who%20are%20leading%20the%20anti-junta%20front%20with%20both%20grit%20and%20sophistication.%20When%20the%20junta%20falls%2C%20which%20should%20be%20soon%2C%20it%20is%20this%20leadership%20that%20will%20take%20charge%20of%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20affairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECentralisation%20of%20decision-making%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%2C%20under%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20decision-making%20on%20Myanmar%20%E2%80%93%20like%20on%20many%20other%20fronts%20%E2%80%93%20has%20become%20overly%20centralised.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20it%20has%20become%20heavily%20securitised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20rests%20on%20a%20few%20senior%20figureheads%2C%20among%20whom%20the%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20(NSA)%2C%20his%20two%20deputies%2C%20Chief%20of%20Defence%20Staff%20(CDS)%2C%20and%20the%20General%20Officer%20Commanding-in-Chief%20(GOC-in-C)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Army%E2%80%99s%20Eastern%20Command%20play%20critical%20roles.%20These%20offices%20have%20always%20been%20pivotal%20in%20shaping%20India%E2%80%99s%20neighbourhood%20policies.%20But%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20through%20bureaucratic%20restructuring%2C%20has%20made%20some%20of%20them%20even%20more%20powerful.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20elevated%20the%20NSA%20%E2%80%93%20Ajit%20Doval%20%E2%80%93%20to%20cabinet%20rank%2C%20allowing%20him%20to%20call%20the%20shots%20on%20a%20host%20of%20issues%20that%20were%20earlier%20outside%20of%20his%20office%E2%80%99s%20remit.%20It%20has%20also%20created%20the%20CDS%E2%80%99%20post%20from%20scratch.%20Although%20the%20CDS%20cannot%20override%20decisions%20taken%20by%20individual%20service%20chiefs%2C%20she%2Fhe%20can%20informally%20dismiss%20their%20considerations.%20Since%20the%20CDS%20is%20the%20highest-ranking%20military%20officer%20in%20the%20system%2C%20service%20chiefs%20could%20find%20it%20difficult%20to%20reject%20her%2Fhis%20advice.%20Such%20a%20structure%20risks%20creating%20a%20closed%20feedback%20loop.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20(MEA)%20is%20also%20involved%20in%20crafting%20India%E2%80%99s%20Myanmar%20policy.%20But%2C%20it%20seems%20to%20be%20doing%20little%20more%20than%20delivering%20soft%20statements%20on%20restoration%20of%20democracy%20and%20protection%20of%20border%20security%2C%20maintaining%20a%20diplomatic%20presence%20in%20Yangon%2C%20hosting%20the%20occasional%20cultural%20functions%20and%20business%20conclaves%20at%20the%20embassy%2C%20and%20facilitating%20secretarial-level%20engagement%20with%20the%20junta%E2%80%99s%20senior%20leadership.%20All%20routine%2C%20low-stakes%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20another%20ministry%20appears%20to%20be%20more%20closely%20involved%20in%20decision-making%20around%20Myanmar%20than%20the%20MEA%3A%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20last%20week%2C%20union%20home%20minister%2C%20Amit%20Shah%2C%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Findia-border-with-myanmar-to-be-protected-like-bangladesh-amit-shah-9119018%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0announced%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20the%20India-Myanmar%20border%20would%20be%20sealed%20and%20the%20Free%20Movement%20Regime%20(FMR)%20scrapped%2C%20a%20move%20that%20would%20effectively%20bar%20asylum%20seekers%20fleeing%20the%20junta%E2%80%99s%20violence%20from%20seeking%20refuge%20in%20India.%20In%20August%2C%20he%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Famit-shah-blames-unrest-in-neighbouring-myanmar-for-manipur-bloodshed-2641417%5C%22%3E%C2%A0linked%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20crisis%20in%20Manipur%20to%20Kuki%20refugees%20from%20Myanmar.%20In%20October%202022%2C%20Shah%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Famit-shah-blames-unrest-in-neighbouring-myanmar-for-manipur-bloodshed-2641417%5C%22%3E%C2%A0claimed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20%E2%80%9CMyanmar%20citizens%E2%80%9D%20were%20opening%20bank%20accounts%20in%20Manipur.%20Finally%2C%20it%20was%20his%20ministry%20that%2C%20just%20a%20month%20after%20the%20coup%20in%20February%202021%2C%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fstop-illegal-influx-from-myanmar-mha-tells-ne-states%2Farticle34054308.ece%5C%22%3E%C2%A0asked%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0border%20states%20in%20the%20Northeast%20to%20stop%20refugees%20from%20coming%20in%20(a%20decision%20that%20was%20later%20withdrawn).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20these%20issues%20fall%20within%20the%20home%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20mandate.%20But%2C%20the%20tone%20and%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20home%20minister%20has%20iterated%20them%20convey%20a%20clear%20message%3A%20as%20far%20as%20the%20dire%20situation%20in%20Myanmar%20is%20concerned%2C%20New%20Delhi%20is%20only%20bothered%20about%20its%20security%20implications%20on%20India%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20devastating%20humanitarian%20consequences%20on%20the%20people%20of%20Myanmar.%20In%20many%20ways%2C%20this%20negates%20the%20relatively%20more%20humanitarian%2C%20pro-democracy%20tone%20that%20the%20MEA%20has%20taken%20in%20many%20of%20its%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20the%20all-powerful%20home%20ministry%20shares%20joint%20control%20of%20the%20Assam%20Rifles%2C%20which%20guards%20the%20India-Myanmar%20border%2C%20with%20the%20defence%20ministry.%20This%20allows%20it%20to%20directly%20shape%20India%E2%80%99s%20posture%20along%20the%20border%2C%20which%20is%20critical%20to%20the%20current%20situation%20in%20Myanmar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20processes%20of%20recalibration%20of%20influence%20and%20concentration%20of%20power%20have%20had%20two%20net%20outcomes%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20Myanmar%20policy%3A%20one%2C%20decision-making%20has%20tilted%20towards%20the%20defence-and-security%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20political%2C%20side%20of%20things%3B%20and%20two%2C%20decision-making%20has%20become%20opaque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20have%20had%20three%20second-order%20consequences%3A%20one%2C%20because%20of%20the%20heavily%20securitised%20approach%2C%20values%20of%20democracy%2C%20justice%20and%20human%20rights%20have%20fallen%20further%20down%20to%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20decision-making%20pyramid%20in%20New%20Delhi%3B%20two%2C%20intelligence-level%20inputs%2C%20which%20often%20precisely%20reflect%20the%20shifting%20ground%20realities%20next%20door%2C%20are%20not%20adding%20up%20to%20commensurate%20decision-making%20at%20the%20highest%20levels%20in%20the%20government%3B%20and%20three%2C%20the%20system%20isn%E2%80%99t%20absorbing%20a%20broad%20enough%20set%20of%20critical%20recommendations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIdeological%20drivers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeopolitical%20interests%20or%20even%20domestic%20systemic%20factors%20don%E2%80%99t%20adequately%20answer%20why%20India%20remains%20a%20fast%20friend%20to%20the%20junta%20in%20Myanmar.%20One%20has%20to%20scratch%20on%20and%20dig%20deeper%20to%20identify%20the%20core%20ideas%20that%20shape%20foreign%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20after%202014%20isn%E2%80%99t%20the%20India%20of%20yore.%20The%20dominant%20ideological%20framework%20of%20mainstream%20politics%20has%20shifted%20dramatically.%20Simply%20speaking%2C%20India%2C%20under%20Modi%2C%20has%20moved%20towards%20the%20right.%20It%20has%20metamorphosed%20from%20a%20secular%20to%20a%20majoritarian%2C%20counter-pluralistic%20democracy.%20As%20an%20inevitable%20byproduct%2C%20authoritarianism%20has%20crept%20into%20daily%20political%20practice.%20Ethno-religious%20minorities%20have%20found%20themselves%20at%20the%20sharpest%20end%20of%20this%20fatal%20devolution.%20Critical%20thought%20is%20being%20discouraged%20through%20suppression%20of%20dissenting%20voices%2C%20free%20media%2C%20NGOs%2C%20and%20even%20think-tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20of%20these%20trends%20and%20tendencies%20are%20equally%20conspicuous%20in%20junta-ruled%20Myanmar.%20The%20military%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3Estyle%20of%20doing%20politics%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%93%20not%20so%20much%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20is%20in%20the%20business%20of%20politics%20%E2%80%93%20probably%20has%20many%20silent%20takers%20in%20India.%20Hindutva%20provocateurs%20close%20to%20ruling%20party%20figures%20have%20even%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fharidwar-anti-muslim-hate-speech-laws-broken%5C%22%3Edirectly%20referenced%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0violence%20perpetrated%20by%20the%20Burmese%20army%20against%20Rohingya%20Muslims%20of%20Myanmar%20to%20rationalise%20their%20own%20sectarian%20rhetoric.%20The%20congruences%20of%20political%20thought%20and%20practice%20are%20uncanny.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20do%20not%20imply%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20pro-junta%20policy%20is%20purely%20driven%20by%20ideological%20overlaps.%20After%20all%2C%20even%20supposedly%20secular%20Congress%20governments%20in%20the%20past%20have%20worked%20with%20military%20regimes%20in%20Myanmar%2C%20often%20looking%20away%20from%20their%20abuses.%20It%20does%2C%20however%2C%20mean%20that%20New%20Delhi%20would%20now%20likely%20be%20even%20less%20invested%20in%20rooting%20for%20democracy%20in%20Myanmar%2C%20let%20alone%20intervening%20to%20displace%20the%20junta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20this%20goes%20beyond%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%E2%80%99s%20majoritarian%20political%20ideology.%20The%20hesitation%20to%20formally%20engage%20the%20pro-democracy%20side%20in%20Myanmar%2C%20which%20includes%20several%20armed%20groups%2C%20is%20rooted%20in%20the%20Indian%20state%E2%80%99s%20own%20experience%20of%20dealing%20with%20insurgencies%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20in%20Northeast%20India%2C%20Kashmir%2C%20and%20central%20India.%20In%20most%20cases%2C%20using%20brute%20force%20and%20imposing%20states%20of%20exception%20(such%20as%20the%20Armed%20Forces%20Special%20Powers%20Act)%20has%20been%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20first%20response%20to%20insurgencies%2C%20many%20of%20which%20were%20explicitly%20secessionist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20long%20history%20of%20battling%20anti-state%20rebellions%20has%20infused%20a%20natural%20revulsion%20for%20armed%20movements%20in%20the%20Indian%20state%E2%80%99s%20mind.%20While%20pro-democracy%20armed%20groups%20in%20Myanmar%20today%20do%20not%20espouse%20secessionism%20and%20largely%20operate%20within%20the%20ethical%20bounds%20of%20a%20just%20war%2C%20New%20Delhi%2C%20deep%20inside%2C%20remains%20suspicious%20of%20them.%20Parts%20of%20the%20current%20government%20and%20defence%20establishment%20probably%20even%20believe%20that%20they%20deserve%20to%20be%20dealt%20with%20force.%20Going%20by%20this%2C%20one%20could%20argue%20that%20India%20would%20openly%20engage%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20armed%20groups%20only%20when%20their%20leaders%20join%20the%20mainstream%20political%20fray.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20major%20exception%20to%20this%20rule%20was%20India%E2%80%99s%20open%20support%20for%20Mukti%20Bahini%2C%20the%20armed%20resistance%20front%20that%20successfully%20secured%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20independence%20from%20Pakistan%20in%201971.%20In%20that%20case%2C%20however%2C%20India%20had%20a%20specific%20strategic%20reason%3A%20the%20imperative%20to%20defeat%20an%20%E2%80%9Cenemy%20state%E2%80%9D%20in%20its%20eastern%20neighbourhood.%20In%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20New%20Delhi%20does%20not%20see%20the%20entity%20that%20the%20armed%20groups%20are%20fighting%20%E2%80%93%20the%20junta%20%E2%80%93%20as%20its%20%E2%80%9Cenemy%E2%80%9D.%20The%20difference%20is%20decisive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20then%2C%20begs%20the%20(rhetorical)%20question%3A%20is%20India%20not%20supporting%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20armed%20revolutionary%20groups%20simply%20because%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20betray%20an%20old%20friend%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20is%20the%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3Evishwa%20mitra%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20latest%20book%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EWhy%20Bharat%20Matters%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Indian%20foreign%20minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20argues%20that%20India%20today%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgreat%20contributor%20to%20solutions%2C%20regional%20or%20global.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20marks%20its%20emergence%20as%C2%A0%3Cem%3Evishwa%20mitra%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20partner%20of%20the%20world%20that%20is%20making%20a%20great%20difference%20with%20each%20passing%20year%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20writes.%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20conveyed%20the%20same%20message%20at%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fmaharashtra%2Fworld-is-seeing-the-rise-of-a-vishwa-mitra-in-india-pm-narendra-modi-2796498%5C%22%3Enavy%20event%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20who%20do%20not%20speak%20or%20read%20Hindi%2C%20which%20would%20cover%20most%20of%20the%20population%20in%20Myanmar%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3Evishwa%20mitra%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eliterally%20translates%20to%20%E2%80%9Cfriend%20of%20the%20world.%E2%80%9D%20One%20wonders%20aloud%20where%20is%20that%20%E2%80%9Cfriend%E2%80%9D%20when%20a%20close%20neighbour%20that%20shares%20a%201640%20km-long%20border%20with%20India%20needs%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fexclusive%2Fnews%2Fs-jaishankar-details-how-foreign-policy-transformed-during-modi-era-757849%5C%22%3ENDTV%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%2031%20January%2C%20Jainshankar%2C%20citing%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9CNeighbourhood%20First%20Policy%E2%80%9D%2C%20further%20emphasised%20that%20India%20has%20developed%20%E2%80%9Creal%20friendships%E2%80%9D%2C%20rather%20than%20transactional%20relationships%2C%20with%20its%20neighbours%20since%202014.%20Where%20is%20that%20%E2%80%9Creal%20friendship%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20people%20of%20Myanmar%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Modi%20government%20needs%20to%20confront%20a%20hard%20truth%3A%20continued%20friendship%20with%20the%20Burmese%20junta%20has%20harmed%20India%E2%80%99s%20interests.%20The%20coup%20has%20wreaked%20havoc%20along%20the%20border%20by%20pushing%20refugees%20into%20the%20Northeast%2C%20opening%20up%20new%20contraband%20routes%2C%20and%20causing%20constant%20panic%20among%20the%20population%20living%20in%20border%20areas.%20Hlaing%E2%80%99s%20regime%20continues%20to%20consciously%20harbour%20anti-India%20militant%20groups%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Frecruitment-spikes-across-insurgent-outfits-in-manipur-more-than-when-insurgency-was-at-its-peak%2F1945527%2F%5C%22%3Esome%20of%20whom%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0have%20been%20adding%20to%20the%20troubles%20in%20strife-torn%20Manipur.%20India%E2%80%99s%20key%20development%20projects%20remain%20stalled%20and%20its%20commercial%20investments%20are%20stuck%20in%20a%20pit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20been%20made%20to%20believe%20that%20this%20is%20an%20India%20that%20will%20stand%20up%20for%20itself%20and%20do%20everything%20in%20its%20capacity%20to%20protect%20its%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20interests.%E2%80%9D%20But%2C%20on%20Myanmar%2C%20where%20India%E2%80%99s%20core%20interests%20stand%20threatened%20by%20an%20impudent%20and%20barbaric%20military%20regime%2C%20we%20are%20yet%20to%20see%20the%20diplomatic%20bravado%20that%20senior%20figures%20in%20the%20current%20government%2C%20including%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20himself%2C%20have%20projected%20in%20their%20public%20iterations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20policy%20wonks%20today%20would%20call%20India%E2%80%99s%20Myanmar%20policy%20a%20case%20of%20%E2%80%9Cstrategic%20restraint.%E2%80%9D%20But%2C%20even%20in%20the%20sobering%20business%20of%20geopolitics%2C%20there%20is%20a%20fine%20line%20beyond%20which%20%E2%80%9Cstrategic%20restraint%E2%80%9D%20starts%20looking%20like%20%E2%80%9Cstrategic%20indifference.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAngshuman%20Choudhury%20is%20an%20associate%20fellow%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20Policy%20Research%2C%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbarbedwires.substack.com%2Fp%2Fthree-years-of-coup-in-myanmar-what%3Futm_campaign%3Dpost%26utm_medium%3Dweb%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%20Substack%20page%2C%20%E2%80%98Barbed%20Wires%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706777130000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01133523%2F1500187623-india-myanmar.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fthree-years-of-coup-in-myanmar-what-explains-indias-pro-junta-position%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Why%20won't%20New