0Moscow%20pay%20compensation%20to%20victims%20as%20requested%20by%20Kyiv.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fukraine-v-russia-a-potential-game-changing-lawsuit-comes-before-the-icj%2Fa-37806132%5C%22%3EUkraine%20asked%20the%20ICJ%20to%20find%20Russia%20guilty%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20breaching%20obligations%20under%20two%20UN%20treaties%2C%C2%A0which%20both%20countries%20signed%2C%20and%20order%20it%20to%20pay%20reparations%20to%20Ukrainian%20civilians%20caught%20up%20in%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20war%20of%20aggression%20as%20well%20as%20to%20the%20families%20of%20victims%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fflight-mh17%2Ft-17910792%5C%22%3Ethe%20Malaysia%20Airlines%20downing%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20did%20the%20court%20say%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20court%20ruled%20that%20under%20the%20terms%20of%20the%20international%20convention%20on%20terrorism%20financing%2C%20only%20cash%20transfers%20could%20be%20considered%20support%20for%20alleged%20terrorist%20groups.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20ICJ%20opinion%20said%2C%20this%20%E2%80%9Cdoes%20not%20include%20the%20means%20used%20to%20commit%20acts%20of%20terrorism%2C%20including%20weapons%20or%20training%20camps.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CConsequently%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20opinion%20continued%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20alleged%20supply%20of%20weapons%20to%20various%20armed%20groups%20operating%20in%20Ukraine%E2%80%A6%20fall%20outside%20the%20material%20scope%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20anti-terrorism%20financing%20convention.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EUltimately%2C%20the%20ICJ%20rejected%20most%20of%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20pleas%2C%20finding%20only%20that%20Russia%20was%2C%20%E2%80%9Cfailing%20to%20take%20measures%20to%20investigate%20facts%E