%20different%20visual%20restatements%20across%20India%2C%20particularly%20in%20Maharashtra%2C%20and%20this%20statue%20made%20by%20a%20Sir%20Jamsetjee%20Jeejeebhoy%20School%20of%20Art%20alumnim%20Jaideep%20Apte%2C%20was%20no%20different.%20Grounded%20in%20European%20academic%20realism%20taught%20at%20the%20school%20since%20the%20mid%2019th%20century%2C%20where%20the%20focus%20is%20on%20learning%20the%20formal%20conventions%20of%20colonial%20representational%20forms%2C%20the%20grammar%20of%20academic%20body%20types%20was%20so%20internalised%20by%20the%20sculptor%20that%20he%20needed%20no%20visual%20model%20for%20his%20figurative%20interpretation.%20Through%20an%20interview%20given%20to%20me%2C%20I%20however%20learnt%20that%20the%20sculptor%20had%20given%20much%20thought%20to%20the%20figure%E2%80%99s%20directional%20symbolism.%20Facing%20north-west%2C%20the%20statue%20was%20aligned%20with%20great%20care%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20sword%20wielding%20warrior%20king%E2%80%99s%20sword-tip%20pointed%20outwards%20and%20away%20from%20the%20landmass%20of%20India%20and%20towards%20where%20sea-borne%20armies%20of%20potential%20colonisers%20would%20arrive%20in%20the%20past%2C%20and%20also%20a%20port%20city%20across%20the%20Arabian%20Sea%20where%20the%20Indian%20Navy%20had%20carried%20out%20its%20%E2%80%98Operation%20Trident%E2%80%99%20on%20December%204-5%2C%201971%2C%20a%20date%20that%20eventually%20came%20to%20be%20designated%20as%20Indian%20Navy%20Day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20many%20projects%2C%20implemented%20in%20great%20haste%20to%20impact%20public%20memory%20in%20the%20upcoming%20election%20year%2C%20the%20process%20of%20making%20the%20sculpture%20was%20accelerated%20through%20the%20use%20of%20laser%20cutting%20machines%20and%203D%20printers%20provided%20literally%20overnight%20by%20a%20firm%20called%20Dream2reality%2C%20to%20print%20out%20the%20enlarged%20scan%20in%20pieces%20and%20sand%20cast%20it%20in%20two%20facilities%20in%20the%20Mumbai%20metropolitan%20region.%3